“The Daily Show With Trevor Noah” has a new job for Sen. Ted Cruz. After the Texas Republican inadvertently boosted an anti-racism children’s book by slamming it during Supreme Court nominee Ketanji Brown Jackson’s confirmation hearings, the Comedy Central show launched a spoof company in his name. Introducing… “Cruz Missile PR.” It’s “the only PR agency that guarantees it can get Ted Cruz to condemn your book,” comedian Michael Kosta says in a parody ad. Find out the different packages available from the faux firm here: